When I was 13, I hated my hair. I didn’t know how to care for curls, and I was annoyed that my sister got the straight hair genes. I begged my mom to let me get the Japanese straightening treatment. For years after, I kept straightening it, hoping it would make me feel prettier and more “put together.” But all it really did was insanely damage my hair and I lost how voluminous my hair used to be. 

13 years later, I’ve taken the time to heal my hair and my relationship with it. Now I genuinely love exploring new ways to style and care for my curls. Hair care turned from a frustrating process to a form of self-love. It’s wild how something I used to hate is now one of my favorite parts of me.

#curlyhair #curlyhairjourney #embraceyourcurls #curlyhaircare #curlyhaircommunity #curlynaturalhair #curlsofinstagram
